@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "MAIN"

Introduction:

Multitudinous is Shareware, when you register you will recive the full 
Blitz Basic source code.

  Multitudinous is  a  program-selector Disk or HD-Menu.  With
Multitudinous programs can be started very easy by selecting gadgets with
your mouse.  The Editor is a  separate  program. 

When  Multitudinous is run for  the  first  time,  it will search your
Fonts: directory for its fonts.  These are called 'Topaz.font 8 & 11' ,
'GTBMenu.Font 8', '2001', and helvetica. If it can't find them, it will 
alert you to the fact and then abort.

  It also looks  for a file named  'M.config' in the MConfigs: Directory. 
If 'M.Config' wasn't found, it wiil alert you of the fact and abort. You 
can edit 'M.Config' BUT DO NOT RENAME IT?


 You will now  be  presented with the main screen containing 60 Gadgets.

        You are now ready to use Multitudinous..

How to start Multitudinous:

The easiest  way  to  start  Multitudinous  is  by  putting  it  into the 
WBStartup-drawer on the  boot-harddisk or WorkBench disk.  It will be
started automatically  after each reset.

